nload PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4398257\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4398257\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 30, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fxi1688449052174.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fxi1688449052174.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fxi1688449052174.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"axi1665702628081\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\"> ucheckbox (CheckBox)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"axi1665702628081__ucheckboxcheckbox__367463\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">ucheckbox</code> widget enables the user to set a Boolean value in a\n      form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called CheckBox, which is mapped to\n         <code class=\"ph codeph\">ucheckbox</code>. </p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"axi1665702628081__p_d112457e1_d112458e1_d112459e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"axi1665702628081__fig_w8547ab1b5b3b1_w8548ab1b5b3_w8549ab1b5_w8550ab1\">\n<img alt=\"CheckBox widget, selected\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/ucheckboxfrm.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"akm1704707836734.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/akm1704707836734.html\" title=\"By default, Uniface displays most fields as edit boxes, but you can change this by selecting a different widget and optionally setting its widget properties. You can do this at the model level, for example in modeled entities or modeled components, or you can do this in the components themselves.\">Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13328e1_d13329e1_d13330e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Overview</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Logical widget name: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> CheckBox </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Maps to physical widget: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ucheckbox</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default definition: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CheckBox=ucheckbox(font=label;fittotext=true)</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Use for: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Boolean fields </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported triggers: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"voy1665703030240.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/voy1665703030240.html\">Triggers</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported properties: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vbe1665702841258.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vbe1665702841258.html\" title=\"Each widget has an associated set of properties that affect how the data is presented in the user interface. These properties can be set in the usys.ini file, in object definitions, and in script.\">Widget Properties</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported in <p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">egrid</code>\n</p>(Grid) widget? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Yes. Some properties may not be applicable.\n                        <p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"clg1695282025414.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/clg1695282025414.html\" title=\"The egrid widget displays data in a tabular format, in which the rows are occurrences of an entity and the columns are fields. It is an entity-level widget that is only applicable to form components.\">egrid (Grid)</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jaw1718600633504.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jaw1718600633504.html\" title=\"The Check Box, Color Box, Combo Box, Command Button, Drop-Down List, Edit Box, Picture, and Spin Button are supported in the Grid widget, but many of their properties are not.\">Widgets and Properties Supported in Grid Widget</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supports Accessibility? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Yes, for testing purposes and screen readers only.\n                     For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"abr1688541158363.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/abr1688541158363.html\" title=\"Uniface exposes the UI of generated Windows desktop applications to screen readers and automation tools for a number of widgets. By exposing the underlying infrastructure, screen readers and automated testing tools can target supported UI elements, and retrieve information regarding their name, value, and status. For these purposes, a mixture of two different technologies has been used - UI Automation and MSAA (Microsoft Active Accessibility).\">Accessibility</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"axi1665702628081__topic_d79622e1_d79623e1_d79624e1_d79625e1_d79626e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d830090e228\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"axi1665702628081__p_d112463e1_d112464e1_d112465e1\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Tri-state</span> property\n            determines whether the allowed check box values can be boolean (two states allowed), or\n            tri-state (three states allowed). The possible values of a check box are\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code>, and a third state that you can\n            attribute any meaning to (for example, default or undetermined). You can also attribute\n            any meaning you want to the values <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"axi1665702628081__p_d112466e1_d112467e1_d112468e1\">You can test for the following values of a check\n            box.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13331e1_d13332e1_d13333e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Valid Values for Check Boxes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13331e1_d13332e1_d13333e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Value</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13331e1_d13332e1_d13333e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13331e1_d13332e1_d13333e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"0\"</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13331e1_d13332e1_d13333e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Cleared, meaning <code class=\"ph codeph\">FALSE</code>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13331e1_d13332e1_d13333e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"1\"</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13331e1_d13332e1_d13333e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Selected, meaning <code class=\"ph codeph\">TRUE</code>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13331e1_d13332e1_d13333e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"\"</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13331e1_d13332e1_d13333e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Tri-state only: <code class=\"ph codeph\">NULL</code>, meaning undetermined.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"axi1665702628081__topic_d79627e1_d79628e1_d79629e1_d79630e1_d79631e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d830090e353\"> Triggers </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"axi1665702628081__li_d43301e1_d43302e1_d43303e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bqj1665702585000.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bqj1665702585000.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to an interactive event on a field or entity widget, such as the user clicking on the field.\">trigger detail</a>—activated for a two-state check box if the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Use Detail Trigger</span> property is set. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"axi1665702628081__li_d43304e1_d43305e1_d43306e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kke1665702605570.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kke1665702605570.html\" title=\"Interactive trigger for that determines what happens after a user changes the value of a field in a form component.\">trigger valueChanged</a>—activated when a user clicks the check box. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"axi1665702628081__topic_d79632e1_d79633e1_d79634e1_d79635e1_d79636e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d830090e385\"> Widget Properties </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Check Box Widget Properties</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Property</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Technical Name</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Dynamic?</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"txj1665702628158.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/txj1665702628158.html\" title=\"This property determines whether a three-dimensional appearance is applied when the widget is displayed. True (default) or False.\">3-D Effect (3d)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">3D</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bou1665702610816.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bou1665702610816.html\" title=\"The Attach to Window Border (Attach) widget property attaches the widget (or area frame) to one or more form window borders or split bars at runtime. This allows the element to be resized or moved when the window is resized or a split bar moved.\">Attach to Window Border (attach)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Attach</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rwc1665702587483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rwc1665702587483.html\" title=\"Color to use as the background of the object.\">Background Color (BackColor)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">BackColor</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rbp1665702587714.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rbp1665702587714.html\" title=\"Color to use as the foreground (usually the text color).\">Foreground Color (ForeColor)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">ForeColor</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yog1665702628229.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yog1665702628229.html\" title=\"Determines how the Checkbox shows that it has focus.\">FocusIndicator</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">FocusIndicator</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rsh1665702628298.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rsh1665702628298.html\" title=\"Determines whether the check box size is set to 1 cell to avoid display problems. True or False (default)\">Fit to Text</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">FitToText</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fcv1665702609942.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fcv1665702609942.html\" title=\"Determines whether the background and foreground colors of the parent entity or form can be inherited. This property can be set in ProcScript for the widgets, but not for labels. Valid Values are True or False (default).\">Inherit Colors (InheritColors)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">InheritColors</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mdg1665702628370.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mdg1665702628370.html\" title=\"Font for the label associated with this widget. The specified label font is also used in widgets that support tool tip text. If not specified, the font definition in the application's .ini file is used.\">Label Font ( LabelFont)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Font</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ewz1665702628443.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ewz1665702628443.html\" title=\"Image used when the mouse pointer is positioned over the widget. The default depends on the widget.\">Mouse Pointer ( Cursor)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Cursor</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qff1665702581606.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qff1665702581606.html\" title=\"Defines the position and size of a rectangle to use as an anchor for a popup form, in character cells or pixels. The default value is 0,0,0,0.\">Popup Rectangle (PopupRect)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">PopupRect</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gbk1665702628600.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gbk1665702628600.html\" title=\"This property specifies the text to be displayed when the cursor is positioned over the widget. It can be a string up to 1024 bytes.\">Tool Tip Text (ToolTipText)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">ToolTipText</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kvj1665702609788.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvj1665702609788.html\" title=\"Determines whether the widget is transparent.\">Transparency</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Transparency</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tjw1665702628672.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tjw1665702628672.html\" title=\"This property determines whether the CheckBox has three states (tri-state) or just two. True or False (default).\">Tri-State</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">TriState</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n<p class=\"p\">No for CHUI</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rld1665702628742.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rld1665702628742.html\" title=\"This property determines whether the detail trigger (as opposed to the valueChanged trigger) is activated when the user clicks the widget.\">Use Detail Trigger</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">V52</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n<p class=\"p\">No for CHUI</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"unc1665702628814.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unc1665702628814.html\" title=\"This property specifies how the check box is aligned in character mode. Left or Right (default).\">Alignment</a> (CHUI only)</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Alignment</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iqs1665702628884.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iqs1665702628884.html\" title=\"This property determines whether the widget is displayed within square brackets; it is applicable only in character mode. Valid values are Yes (default), No, or Fit.\">Decoration</a> (CHUI only)</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Decoration</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"axi1665702628081__table_d13334e1_d13335e1_d13336e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jyu1665702617660.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>UIState</a><p>Control whether keyboard accelerators and focus are displayed in selected widgets under Microsoft Windows.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tqa1665703220633.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$CHECK_BOX</a><p>Set the video attributes for a check box in character mode.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4398257\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4398257\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ucheckbox (CheckBox) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 30, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 ucheckbox (CheckBox) The ucheckbox widget enables the user to set a Boolean value in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called CheckBox, which is mapped to ucheckbox . For more information, see Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity . Table 1. Widget Overview Logical widget name: CheckBox Maps to physical widget: ucheckbox Default definition: CheckBox=ucheckbox(font=label;fittotext=true) Use for: Boolean fields Supported triggers: See Triggers Supported properties: See Widget Properties Supported in egrid (Grid) widget? Yes. Some properties may not be applicable. For more information, see egrid (Grid) and Widgets and Properties Supported in Grid Widget . Supports Accessibility? Yes, for testing purposes and screen readers only. For more information, see Accessibility . Description The Tri-state property determines whether the allowed check box values can be boolean (two states allowed), or tri-state (three states allowed). The possible values of a check box are True or False , and a third state that you can attribute any meaning to (for example, default or undetermined). You can also attribute any meaning you want to the values on and off . You can test for the following values of a check box. Table 2. Valid Values for Check Boxes Value Description \"0\" Cleared, meaning FALSE . \"1\" Selected, meaning TRUE . \"\" Tri-state only: NULL , meaning undetermined. Triggers trigger detail —activated for a two-state check box if the Use Detail Trigger property is set. trigger valueChanged —activated when a user clicks the check box. Widget Properties Table 3. Check Box Widget Properties Property Technical Name Dynamic? 3-D Effect (3d) 3D No Attach to Window Border (attach) Attach Yes Background Color (BackColor) BackColor Yes Foreground Color (ForeColor) ForeColor Yes FocusIndicator FocusIndicator Yes Fit to Text FitToText No Inherit Colors (InheritColors) InheritColors Yes Label Font ( LabelFont) Font Yes Mouse Pointer ( Cursor) Cursor Yes Popup Rectangle (PopupRect) PopupRect Yes Tool Tip Text (ToolTipText) ToolTipText Yes Transparency Transparency Yes Tri-State TriState Yes No for CHUI Use Detail Trigger V52 Yes No for CHUI Alignment (CHUI only) Alignment No Decoration (CHUI only) Decoration No Related Links UIState Control whether keyboard accelerators and focus are displayed in selected widgets under Microsoft Windows. $CHECK_BOX Set the video attributes for a check box in character mode. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}